  "title": "Senior DevOps Engineer ( AWS|Linux)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Employment: </strong> 1 year contract/ Renewable<br /><strong>Salary  :  </strong>Attractive package & Benefits</p><p><strong>About the Role</strong><br />We are looking for a S<strong>enior Technical Architect</strong> to join our client. You will play a key role in designing cloud solutions on AWS, supporting application deployments, enabling cross-platform environments, and ensuring systems run reliably in production. This is an excellent opportunity for cloud architects or DevOps engineers with <strong>5+ years of hands-on experience</strong> in AWS, cloud solutioning, and server management.</p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><p><ul><li>Design and implement secure, scalable, and reliable AWS-based solutions.</li><li>Translate business and technical requirements into architectural specifications.</li><li>Support and manage IIS environments for hosting enterprise web applications.</li><li>Work with database teams to optimize Oracle DB configurations and performance.</li><li>Administer and troubleshoot Linux-based systems and applications.</li><li>Lead and support deployment processes from development to production environments.</li><li>Provide ongoing production support to ensure application performance and uptime.</li><li>Participate in architectural reviews and help define cloud best practices and standards.</li><li>Maintain documentation of solutions, configurations, and architecture.</li><li>Keep current with cloud, infrastructure, and system design trends and emerging tech.</li><li>Participate in maintenance or critical incident activities when needed (after-hours occasionally).</li></ul></p><p><strong>Who You Are</strong></p><p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related fields (or equivalent experience).</li><li>5+ years experience in cloud architecture, DevOps, or cloud infrastructure.</li><li>Strong understanding of AWS cloud services and architecture principles.</li><li>Knowledge of IIS, Oracle Database, and basic SQL queries.</li><li>Experience with Linux OS and command-line usage.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving capabilities with attention to detail.</li><li>Clear verbal and written communication skills.</li><li>Curious, adaptable, and eager to adopt new technologies and methods.</li><li>AWS certifications (Solutions Architect / DevOps Engineer) are highly advantageous.</li></ul></p><p><strong>Bonus Skills (Nice to Have)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Scripting or automation using batch, PowerShell, or SSM documents.</p></li><li><p>Basic programming or scripting (Python, JavaScript, etc.).</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with networking and cloud security best practices.</p></li><li><p>Exposure to architectural frameworks.</p></li><li><p>Experience managing CrushFTP environments is a plus.</p></li></ul>",
